			<description><![CDATA[<p>PRODUCT MARKETING MANAGER (PMM)&nbsp;position reports to the VP, Marketing and Product</p><p>The Product Marketing Manager (PMM) must be able to interface effectively and establish quick credibility and confidence with Sales, Client Services, Engineering, and Direct Customers. This requires an extremely talented and flexible individual with strong presentation skills, adept business knowledge, organizational abilities, and is capable of bridging customer business requirements to technical feature sets and broader market trends &ndash; specific to the mobile market.</p><p>The PMM will help develop marketing plans through market research, competitive analysis, pricing, customer engagement, and business intelligence. The ideal candidate regularly comes up with creative ideas, and has the analytical skills to properly vet them &ndash; including gleaning actionable insights from data.</p><p>REQUIREMENTS:<br />Serve as a product expert; actively participating in the communication of product features and benefits to internal and external audiences</p><p>Extremely detail-oriented and exceptionally organized</p><p>Manages multiple projects and priorities simultaneously</p><p>Proficient with Microsoft PowerPoint, Word and Excel</p><p>Possesses excellent written and verbal communication skills.</p><p>Presents effectively to both individuals and groups at all levels (Account Coordinator to CEO) and in all formats (phone, in person, in presentations)</p><p>Crafts presentation materials that inspire excitement and convey key messages with clarity</p><p>BONUS:</p><p>Experience with photo editing programs such as Photoshop</p><p>Basic technical background (i.e. familiar with HTML, rudimentary understanding of databases; while this position does not include coding or programming, basic technical insights are helpful to discover practical solutions)</p><p>DESIRED ATTRIBUTES:</p><p>Works well with others across multiple teams, marshaling resources to deliver results that exceed internal and external client expectations</p><p>Strong interpersonal skills generate credibility, trust and respect throughout the company</p><p>Must possess a solutions-oriented mindset; finds answers as opposed to simply pointing out problems</p><p>Thrives in a fast-paced, deadline-oriented environment</p><p>Maintains a positive attitude consistently despite challenging situations</p><p>A hands-on participant with a strong work ethic</p><p>Prepared to go &ldquo;above and beyond&rdquo; to get the job done</p><p>Demonstrates passion in his/her work, and for the online medium</p><p>Works independently without constant direct supervision, while knowing how and when to appropriately escalate matters needing management attention</p>]]></description>
